text.section:
When an application for certificate of approval is filed, the Department shall have an investigation made of:
The applicant;
The private group home for which approval is sought;
The facts stated in the application;
The number of other group homes or alternative living units in the neighborhood;
The public utilities and services available; and
The access to transportation, shopping and recreational facilities, and health-related services.

section.section:
The notice shall state:
The name of the applicant;
The type of approval that is sought;
The location of the proposed private group home; and
The time and place that the Secretary sets for the hearing, which shall be at least 7 but not more than 15 days after the last publication of the notice.
